                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2570: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-11T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 8, 4 p.m. Matter has been referred to American Group for discussion
                    and you will be advised decision reached. Repeat to Peking together with your
                    telegram on the subject and request Legation to cable Department full text of
                    Presidential decree of November 22.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
